aggressive /əˈɡrɛsɪv/

1. ADJ An aggressive person or animal has a quality of anger and determination that makes them ready to attack other people. 好斗的 

例： Some children are much more aggressive than others. 一些孩子比其他孩子好斗得多。 

例： These fish are very aggressive. 这些鱼十分好斗。 

2. aggressively ADV 好斗地 

例： They'll react aggressively. 他们会凶猛地作出反应。 

3. ADJ People who are aggressive in their work or other activities behave in a forceful way because they are very eager to succeed. 好强的 

例： He is respected as a very aggressive and competitive executive. 他被尊认为一位十分好强好胜的主管。 

4. aggressively ADV 好强地 

例： ...countries noted for aggressively pursuing energy efficiency. …以拼命追求能效著称的国家。

